  "body": "In `develop`, `/// @why3 ...` comments in the beginning of `.sol` files are used for describing the invariants of the following contract.  As a result, `solc --formal --output-dir tmp` translates these comments into somewhere in the middle of the generated `tmp/solidity.mlw` file.\n\nSometimes, a user wishes to have a prefix in `.mlw` files, like library imports and custom lemmata.  For this purpose, this issue prposes a new pragma `/// @why3-header ...`.\n\nThe lines beginning with `/// @why3-header` are collected in order, and reproduced in the generated `.mlw` file.\n",
